OL,3,CHow inadequate hospital translation
OL,4,Cservices played a part in baby's death
OL,6,FIn a letter sent from Birmingham
OL,7,FWomen's and Children NHS Foundation
OL,8,FTrust to Hazha and Bahroz, the Trust
OL,9,Fsaid: "You should have remained on the
OL,10,Ffetal heart rate monitor and been
OL,11,Ftransferred to Delivery Suite.
OL,13,F"Had we done this, your baby was very
OL,14,Flikely to have been born alive."
OL,16,FThe Trust also admitted that "had
OL,17,Fthere been reasonable care and
OL,18,Ftreatment the baby would not have been
OL,19,Fborn stillborn and would have survived.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/17
