OL,3,CHow inadequate hospital translation
OL,4,Cservices played a part in baby's death
OL,6,FHazha relied on Bahroz to translate
OL,7,Fthe night that Mally died. At one
OL,8,Fpoint, Bahroz was asked to leave his
OL,9,Fwife. He put up a fight and was
OL,10,Feventually allowed to stay.
OL,12,FA recent study by the charity
OL,13,FBirthrights highlights "the problems
OL,14,Fthat can arise when using family
OL,15,Fmembers as interpreters and the need
OL,16,Ffor specially trained interpreters
OL,17,Fwith knowledge in both women's health
OL,18,Fand cultural safety."
OL,20,F"One of the most tragic cases I have
OL,21,Fseen"
